CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 8, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "Pittsburghers Enjoy a Sporting Holiday Weekend - Off The Plank! - Pretty Betty Mae George, women's diving champion, poised precariously atop the high diving board at Highland Park pool before diving gracefully into the water.  She copped the senior AMA fancy diving championship before 8,000 spectators, Labor Day.  Betty Mae retained her title by beating Wilma Fletcher of Clairton, and Laurine Loebig of the Hill Top A. C. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Diving champion Betty Mae George doing handstand at end of diving board at Highland Park swimming pool
